title: ICE: "Span must not be empty and have no suggestion" -Wunused-lifetimes

labels.name: A-diagnostics
labels.description: Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.description: This issue requires debug-assertions in some way

body:
### Code code from `src/test/ui/deriving/issue-89188-gat-hrtb.rs` requires debug assertions ```Rust trait Trait2 { type As; } #[derive(Clone)] struct ShimMethod4(pub &'static dyn for<'s> Fn(&'s mut T::As)); pub fn main() {} ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` commit f90a4ff26c9743abf612f015c4398d7158b646b6 (origin/master, origin/HEAD) Merge: 338cfd3cce4 fb471de5a91 Author: bors Date: Mon Nov 14 03:15:03 2022 +0000 Auto merge of #104188 - jyn514:download-config-only, r=Mark-Simulacrum Make all download functions need only Config, not Builder This also adds a new `mod download` instead of scattering the download code across `config.rs` and `native.rs`. This is the simplest and also most bit-rotty part of https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/102282. Opening it earlier so it's not mixed in with behavior changes and to avoid rebase hell. cc https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/94829 (which nows has the hackmd linked). r? `@Mark-Simulacrum` ``` ### Error output `rustc issue-89188-gat-hrtb.rs -Wunused-lifetimes` ``` ```
